description_url: required in NanoSIMSImageCollection.  Cameca *.im file format is used for storing SIMS (Secondary Ion Mass Spectrometry) data acquired using Cameca SIMS instruments; the format is proprietary to Cameca.  There is open-source software that open .im files: OpenMIMS (https://nano.bwh.harvard.edu/openmims--dead link.  Github source code:https://github.com/BWHCNI/OpenMIMS, no releases, last update 2018; apparently can run with Fiji software, see https://github.com/BWHCNI/OpenMIMS/wiki/Installation); Look@NanoSIMS (http://nanosims.geo.uu.nl/nanosims-wiki/doku.php/nanosims:lans;  Requires Matlab (proprietary software) installed on your system to run).  Python module to read Cameca .im files: https://github.com/zanpeeters/sims; imViewer, avaialble via https://www.lss.ls.tum.de/en/boku/download/tools/nanosims/ (2025-05-04). Cameca commercial software: https://www.cameca.com/service/software/winimage
